 Hall Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA 24450 Email the Office Katrina Butner           Email the Office  Chief of Staff Colonel James P  Inman  86 U S  Army  retired  Colonel Jamie Inman  86 assumed the duties of Chief of Staff on 24 June 2013  As Chief of Staff  Inman is responsible for coordinating the actions of the Institute s primary staff officers and ensuring integration of all organizational and Post operations  events and issues  His additional duties include publishing and maintaining all general orders  special orders  and memoranda  and incoordination with the offices of the Registrar and the Commandant of Cadets for official cadet files  He serves as chair of the Institute Planning Committee  composed of senior VMI executives who issue policy guidance and provide advice to the Superintendent  Colonel Inman is a native of Trenton  Tennessee and he received his Bachelor s Degree in English from the Virginia Military Institute in 1986  He also holds Masters Degrees in Liberal Arts from Louisiana State University and in National Security Strategy from the National Defense University  Colonel Inman s military education includes the Command and General Staff College and the National War College  His most recent assignment prior to retirement was as the Commander of the National Capitol Region Warrior Transition Brigade  In this capacity he was responsible for all Wounded  Ill and Injured Soldiers in the NCR  Other assignments include Chief of Staff  U S  Army Cadet Command  Field Artillery Branch Chief  Human Resources Command  Commander 3rd Battalion  320th Field Artillery 101st Airborne Division  duty at the United States Military Delegation to NATO in Brussels Belgium  and other field artillery assignments as a company and field grade officer  Military awards and decorations that Colonel Inman has received include the Legion of Merit with two oak leaf clusters  Bronze Star Medal with oak leaf cluster  and Purple Heart  He wears US  campaign ribbons for combat duty in Iraq  Afghanistan and Desert Shield Storm  He is also authorized to wear the Air Assault Badge  Senior Parachutist Wings  Ranger Tab and the Joint Staff Identification Badge  Colonel Inman is married to the former Lori L  White of Kilbourne  Louisiana  They have two children  Maria and Eric      Chief of Staff Colonel James P  Inman  86 U S  Army  retired  Colonel Jamie Inman  86 assumed the duties of Chief of Staff on 24 June 2013  As Chief of Staff  Inman is responsible for coordinating the actions of the Institute s primary staff officers and ensuring integration of all organizational and Post operations  events and issues  His additional duties include publishing and maintaining all general orders  special orders  and memoranda  and incoordination with the offices of the Registrar and the Commandant of Cadets for official cadet files  He serves as chair of the Institute Planning Committee  composed of senior VMI executives who issue policy guidance and provide advice to the Superintendent  Colonel Inman is a native of Trenton  Tennessee and he received his Bachelor s Degree in English from the Virginia Military Institute in 1986  He also holds Masters Degrees in Liberal Arts from Louisiana State University and in National Security Strategy from the National Defense University  Colonel Inman s military education includes the Command and General Staff College and the National War College  His most recent assignment prior to retirement was as the Commander of the National Capitol Region Warrior Transition Brigade  In this capacity he was responsible for all Wounded  Ill and Injured Soldiers in the NCR  Other assignments include Chief of Staff  U S  Army Cadet Command  Field Artillery Branch Chief  Human Resources Command  Commander 3rd Battalion  320th Field Artillery 101st Airborne Division  duty at the United States Military Delegation to NATO in Brussels Belgium  and other field artillery assignments as a company and field grade officer  Mil